0.02943514,0.06746662,-0.05117362,0.02277379,-0.01467654,0.08352295,-0.00004296,0.07549293,-0.04578827,0.04606541,0.03294394,0.20734943,-0.03832899,0.01399574,-0.02163569,-0.03430666,0.0007465,0.0944994,0.03953395,0.04544957,0.01805572,0.07807974,0.00758534,-0.01358208,0.00965526,-0.02395692,0.00262744,0.00683689,-0.01353255,0.0011245,0.01782911,-0.02221443,-0.00950535,0.09580048,0.00682632,-0.00863924,-0.02706873,-0.03498268,0.00993302,-0.01267874,-0.03216557,-0.01059197,-0.00524647,0.07453638,0.06082316,-0.00677709,-0.02086798,0.01049468,-0.02954244,-0.01079461,0.0441451,0.05583551,-0.00644388,-0.00221055],"last_embed":{"tokens":434,"hash":"9k7vwd"}}},"last_read":{"hash":"9k7vwd","at":1780964286486},"class_name":"SmartSource","last_import":{"mtime":1780964270220,"size":9444,"at":1780964283891,"hash":"9k7vwd"},"blocks":{"#---frontmatter---":[1,6],"#":[7,7],"#Round 1 Questions":[8,72],"#Round 1 Questions#1. The Core Vision":[10,24],"#Round 1 Questions#1. The Core Vision#What is the main problems i want to solve?":[12,18],"#Round 1 Questions#1. The Core Vision#What is the main problems i want to solve?#{1}":[14,18],"#Round 1 Questions#1. The Core Vision#How would I describe the overall vibe or philosophy of the app?":[19,24],"#Round 1 Questions#1. The Core Vision#How would I describe the overall vibe or philosophy of the app?#{1}":[21,24],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")":[25,42],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#How do you want the financial data to get into the app?":[27,32],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#How do you want the financial data to get into the app?#{1}":[29,32],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#What are the absolute \"must-have\" features for Version 1 (MVP)?":[33,42],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#What are the absolute \"must-have\" features for Version 1 (MVP)?#{1}":[35,42],"#Round 1 Questions#3. User Experience & Design (The \"How it feels\")":[43,44],"#Round 1 Questions#When you open the app, what is the very first piece of information you want to see on your dashboard?":[45,55],"#Round 1 Questions#When you open the app, what is the very first piece of information you want to see on your dashboard?#{1}":[47,50],"#Round 1 Questions#When you open the app, what is the very first piece of information you want to see on your dashboard?#Are there any existing finance apps, websites, or spreadsheets you’ve used that you liked or disliked? What stood out about them?":[51,55],"#Round 1 Questions#When you open the app, what is the very first piece of information you want to see on your dashboard?#Are there any existing finance apps, websites, or spreadsheets you’ve used that you liked or disliked? What stood out about them?#{1}":[53,55],"#Round 1 Questions#4. Tech & Scope (The \"Under the hood\")":[56,57],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?":[58,72],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#{1}":[60,67],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#Is this strictly a desktop web app, or is optimized mobile viewing a priority for quick logging?":[68,72],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#Is this strictly a desktop web app, or is optimized mobile viewing a priority for quick logging?#{1}":[70,72],"#Round 2 Questions":[73,122],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)":[75,86],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The Infinite Scroll Concept:** You mentioned wanting the entire app to feel like one continuous webpage with structural motion and instant navigation animations (likely using a tool like _Framer Motion_).":[77,81],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The Infinite Scroll Concept:** You mentioned wanting the entire app to feel like one continuous webpage with structural motion and instant navigation animations (likely using a tool like _Framer Motion_).#{1}":[78,81],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The \"Health Snapshot\":** For the immediate dashboard view, you want a holistic picture of financial trajectory. If you had to pick the **one main hero metric** at the absolute top of the page, would it be **Net Worth** (past/present) or **Remaining Discretionary Budget** (the day-to-day focus)?":[82,86],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The \"Health Snapshot\":** For the immediate dashboard view, you want a holistic picture of financial trajectory. If you had to pick the **one main hero metric** at the absolute top of the page, would it be **Net Worth** (past/present) or **Remaining Discretionary Budget** (the day-to-day focus)?#{1}":[84,86],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**":[87,100],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**The Manual/CSV Process:** Since Australian open banking can be restrictive, CSV uploads are a smart MVP choice.":[89,93],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**The Manual/CSV Process:** Since Australian open banking can be restrictive, CSV uploads are a smart MVP choice.#{1}":[91,93],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**Account Archetypes:** You want to track everything from neobanks to stocks and managed funds.":[94,100],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**Account Archetypes:** You want to track everything from neobanks to stocks and managed funds.#{1}":[96,100],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**":[101,113],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**Google Stitch:** This is a powerful choice for modern apps, especially when you want to handle secure data workflows, serverless microservices, and tightly integrated AI components without managing massive, clunky backend infrastructure.":[103,106],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**Google Stitch:** This is a powerful choice for modern apps, especially when you want to handle secure data workflows, serverless microservices, and tightly integrated AI components without managing massive, clunky backend infrastructure.#{1}":[105,106],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**State Management & Charts:** Recharts is great, but for highly responsive, \"structural motion\" dashboards, sometimes libraries like _Tremor_ (built on Tailwind) or _nivo_ offer cleaner minimalism out of the box.":[107,113],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**State Management & Charts:** Recharts is great, but for highly responsive, \"structural motion\" dashboards, sometimes libraries like _Tremor_ (built on Tailwind) or _nivo_ offer cleaner minimalism out of the box.#{1}":[109,113],"#Round 2 Questions#**4. The AI Philosophy (Avoiding \"Slop\")**":[114,122],"#Round 2 Questions#**4. The AI Philosophy (Avoiding \"Slop\")**#**Context-Driven AI:** To avoid looking like a generic \"vibe-coded\" app with a random chatbot shoved in the corner, the AI needs to be deeply integrated.":[116,122],"#Round 2 Questions#**4. The AI Philosophy (Avoiding \"Slop\")**#**Context-Driven AI:** To avoid looking like a generic \"vibe-coded\" app with a random chatbot shoved in the corner, the AI needs to be deeply integrated.#{1}":[118,122]},"outlinks":[],"metadata":{"tags":["#Project","#finance","#projects/fin-app/project-doc"]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"key":"01_Projects/fin-app/System requirements - Brainstorm.md"},
